<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A whim; a freak; a capricious notion, a fanciful or
odd conceit.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>whimsies</xex> of poets and
painters.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men's folly, <qex>whimsies</qex>, and inconstancy.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mistaking the <qex>whimseys</qex> of a feverish brain for the calm
revelation of truth.</q> <rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A whim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whimsey</ent>⟦br⟧

